ield Wildcats football|Linfield Wildcats]]'''\n| 15\n| 2000\n| 2019\n| 26\n| 14\n| 40\n| {{Winning percentage|26|14}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Louisiana College Wildcats football|Louisiana College Wildcats]]\n| 1\n| 2012\n| 2012\n| 0\n| 1\n| 1\n| {{Winning percentage|0|1}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Lycoming Warriors football|Lycoming Warriors]]\n| 12\n| 1985\n| 2008\n| 13\n| 12\n| 25\n| {{Winning percentage|13|12}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Macalester Scots football|Macalester Scots]]\n| 1\n| 2014\n| 2014\n| 0\n| 1\n| 1\n| {{Winning percentage|0|1}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Maine Maritime Mariners football|Maine Maritime Mariners]]\n| 1\n| 2009\n| 2009\n| 0\n| 1\n| 1\n| {{Winning percentage|0|1}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| '''[[SUNY Maritime Privateers football|SUNY Maritime Privateers]]'''\n| 2\n| 2010\n| 2019\n| 0\n| 2\n| 2\n| {{Winning percentage|0|2}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| '''[[Martin Luther Knights football|Martin Luther Knights]]'''\n| 2\n| 2018\n| 2019\n| 0\n| 2\n| 2\n| {{Winning percentage|0|2}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| '''[[Mary Hardin\u2013Baylor Crusaders football|Mary Hardin\u2013Baylor Crusaders]]'''\n| 18\n| 2002\n| 2019\n| 43\n| 16\n| 59\n| {{Winning percentage|43|16}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Maryville Scots football|Maryville Scots]]\n| 2\n| 2013\n| 2018\n| 0\n| 1\n| 2\n| {{Winning percentage|0|2}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[UMass Dartmouth Corsairs football|UMass Dartmouth Corsairs]]\n| 1\n| 2002\n| 2002\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| {{Winning percentage|0|1}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| '''[[MIT Engineers football|MIT Engineers]]'''\n| 3\n| 2014\n| 2019\n| 1\n| 3\n| 4\n| {{Winning percentage|1|3}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[McDaniel Green Terror football|McDaniel Green Terror]]\n| 5\n| 1997\n| 2001\n| 2\n| 5\n| 7\n| {{Winning percentage|2|5}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[McMurry War Hawks football|McMurry War Hawks]]\n| 1\n| 2011\n| 2011\n| 1\n| 1\n