tball season navbox}}\n{{National Collegiate Athletic Association}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of college football team records]]\n[[Category:NCAA Division III football|Playoff Appearances]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following is a '''list of current [[NCAA Division III|Division III]] schools that have participated in the playoffs''' leading to the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]] [[NCAA Division III Football Championship|Division III Football Championship]]. The playoffs began with four teams in [[1973 NCAA Division III football season|1973]], expanded to 8 teams to [[1975 NCAA Division III football season|1975]], 16 teams in [[1985 NCAA Division III football season|1985]], 28 teams in [[1999 NCAA Division III football season|1999]], and finally 32 teams in [[2005 NCAA Division III football season|2005]].<ref>{{cite web|title=All-Time Division III Football Championship Records |url=http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/football_champs_records/2013/d3/champ.pdf|work=NCAA|publisher=NCAA.org|accessdate=December 24, 2014|pages=1\u201315}}</ref>\n\n==Current Division III members==\n* Teams in '''bold''' participated in the [[2019 Stagg Bowl|2019 postseason]].\n* Updated through December 20, 2019\n\n<!--Wins/Losses/Total/Pct. updated after playoffs-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Team\n!Appearances\n!First\n!Last\n!Wins\n!Losses\n!Total\n!Pct.\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Adrian Bulldogs football|Adrian Bulldogs]]\n| 4\n| 1983\n| 2014\n| 0\n| 4\n| 4\n| {{Winning percentage|0|4}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Albion Britons football|Albion Britons]]\n| 11\n| 1977\n| 2015\n| 5\n| 10\n| 15\n| {{Winning percentage|5|10}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Albright Lions football|Albright Lions]]\n| 5\n| 1975\n| 2015\n| 4\n| 5\n| 9\n| {{Winning percentage|4|5}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[Alfred Saxons football|Alfred Saxons]]\n| 4\n| 1981\n| 2016\n| 4\n| 4\n| 8\n| {{Winnin